<b>Subject:</b> Well board points out many interesting points on the way system should work and critics are a must!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=780" TARGET=_self>Judged by all (opinion)</A> (Aztor)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Critics will most likely get one of these:

<P>1)answer to problem by guide/gm/player
<BR>2)counter response
<BR>3)read by gm/developer staff & other people
<BR>4)which may cause consideration on wish list....
<P>5)which may cause implementation
<P>so its much better to complain and point out how it will fail so it can be prevented...its same imagine you are climbing a ladder..and I tell you that 35th step is broken ...and so if u dont listen you will step on it and possibly fall down, and get injured..(inrelation with EQ, fall down, lose popularity, unbalanced)
<BR>or you can read my message try to fix/replace the "step" or just warn people to avoid it...sorta bad analogy but im saying that criticism is very constructive here....on PVP forum :)
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
